{{Top|leg}}
'''Random sabacc''' was a type of [[Sabacc/Legends|sabacc]] in which the rules of play changed at random intervals. This particular type of sabacc was played by [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] and [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]] over ownership of the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']] in 11 ABY, during which [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] served as the randomizer.

Because of the wildly varying rules and procedures used during Random sabacc, a scoring system is often used to keep track of progress. During the game between Han and Lando, the two players played to one hundred points, and kept score by giving the winning player an amount of points equal to the difference between the winning and losing hands.

